  "text": "The Kubernetes controller work queue with rate limiting is a sophisticated system implemented in the client-go package at staging/src/k8s.io/client-go/util/workqueue/. The implementation consists of several layered interfaces and implementations:\n\n## Core Interface Hierarchy\n\nThe foundation is the TypedInterface (queue.go:29-37) which defines the basic queue operations: Add(item), Get(), Done(item), Len(), and ShutDown(). This is implemented by the Typed[T] struct in queue.go (lines 188-212).\n\n## Delaying Queue\n\nThe TypedDelayingInterface (delaying_queue.go:36-40) extends TypedInterface with AddAfter(item, duration) capability, allowing items to be requeued with delays. The delayingType[T] struct (delaying_queue.go:153-172) wraps a basic queue and manages a priority queue of delayed items via waitingLoop().\n\n## Rate Limiting Layer\n\nThe TypedRateLimitingInterface (rate_limiting_queue.go:27-40) further extends TypedDelayingInterface with AddRateLimited(item) and Forget(item) methods. It is implemented by rateLimitingType[T] (rate_limiting_queue.go:130-147), which wraps a TypedDelayingInterface and a TypedRateLimiter.\n\n## Rate Limiter Implementations\n\nThe core rate limiter interface TypedRateLimiter[T] (default_rate_limiters.go:30-38) defines When(item), Forget(item), and NumRequeues(item) methods. Key implementations include:\n\n1. **TypedItemExponentialFailureRateLimiter** (default_rate_limiters.go:84-149): Implements exponential backoff using formula baseDelay*2^<num-failures>. Tracks failure counts per item and caps delays at maxDelay.\n\n2. **TypedBucketRateLimiter** (default_rate_limiters.go:62-77): Adapts golang.org/x/time/rate's token bucket algorithm to the workqueue API. Provides a simple global QPS limit regardless of item count.\n\n3. **TypedMaxOfRateLimiter** (default_rate_limiters.go:218-259): Composes multiple limiters and returns the most restrictive delay. Commonly used with NewTypedMaxOfRateLimiter combining ItemExponential 